</title>
<subSubSection id="8759121D586F38B53F64BDE087C1CDCD" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" type="description">
<paragraph id="4C58384506EE1CA55FCFB8DC55A67FE7" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="971F0B36A569B9E78592D3805D051B5A" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis id="967E1B23425DC68186C1A15DEC721750" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="7B1B3FB8D0E1EB11A2E78D53B87AEF8F" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<normalizedToken id="2F9DD7F4831DFF0CF141F56555759397" originalValue="Rispenäste" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Rispenaeste</normalizedToken>
behaart;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="110D6CC3D81285D815EEFC6E70B9198B" originalValue="Ährchen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Aehrchen</normalizedToken>
meist 
<normalizedToken id="B4BFA856011B10A07826C422FB4065E5" originalValue="größer" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">groesser</normalizedToken>
, 2-3 cm lang, 10-15 
<normalizedToken id="4C7DF6B598ECF522AAB407BBE118C952" originalValue="blütig" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">bluetig</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="E4DE8E286304DDDDD74ADE293A45AE48" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
Deckspelzen 10-12 mm lang, etwa um 1,5 mm 
<normalizedToken id="8CE5104CEFCE145FC476C0C41AE4501F" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die Vorspelzen
</emphasis>
. - 
<normalizedToken id="71686F0A8EE70A937D37D1B449A31DCA" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer und Herbst.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19D342BEEE4D9456B88CC3A72CFFDA7B" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="3F3F493E226476B2DE83B28430C6C6C6" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Zytologische Angaben. 2n = 28:</emphasis>
Material aus Frankreich (Cugnac und Simonet 1941).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A0057A498146E7AEF82B326BECA1D17" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="1D20A2EB9F77943FA1ECDE65A6DCF488" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Standort</emphasis>
. Kollin und montan. Wie 
<taxonomicName id="1A58E5D9D2D30FBDC16221E07B5F2D6E" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis id="348F94C79AD3614A3A1B2F5DF91E632D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12). Nach Braun-Blanquet (1949) kommt in 
<normalizedToken id="B9F5022F764823E7423D79AF0A2AFF23" originalValue="Graubünden" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Graubuenden</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName id="BA2A112578D30EEBC2204C7554EF70C3" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis id="D017D512A9562A7B73DDB22491CB3F28" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auf kalkhaltigen, 
<normalizedToken id="A273486485FC9E4031A60A2D12C820B8" originalValue="durchlässigen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">durchlaessigen</normalizedToken>
Schottern in 
<normalizedToken id="41011605F9363E0F91B2E731025385AC" originalValue="heißen" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">heissen</normalizedToken>
, lufttrockenen Lagen im 
<emphasis id="60134BC67814FC703DD30B95DF020A85" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Adonieto-Delphinietum consolidae</emphasis>
Br.-Bl. 1949 vor.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="76D9AE14D7B6B73A6BEC20ECA3D317C8" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">
<emphasis id="F08B4FA9A4D266B67BE51501DD6B8C99" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">Verbreitung. Eurasiatische Pflanze:</emphasis>
Wie 
<taxonomicName id="F37202126D8E93F906D3DD7DA63EB1F0" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Serrafalcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="null" pageNumber="367" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="secalinus">
<emphasis id="BC5B2E237B191F6A9A79C16C24B3DC96" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="367">B. secalinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 12).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
